mixin ButtonGroupDescription
	h4.mt-6.mb-1 Button Group
	p Group a series of buttons together on a single line with the button group, and super-power them with JavaScript.				

mixin ButtonGroupBasic 
	h5.mt-4.mb-1 Basic Example
	p Wrap a series of buttons with
		code .btn
		|  in
		code .btn-group
		| . Add on optional JavaScript radio and checkbox style behaviour with
	+ComponentCard
		.btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Basic example')
			= '\n'
			button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') Left
			= '\n'
			button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') Middle
			= '\n'
			button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') Right
			= '\n'

mixin ButtonToolbar
	h5.mt-4.mb-1 Button Toolbar
	p Combine sets of button groups into button toolbars for more complex components. Use utility classes as needed to space out groups, buttons, and more.
	+ComponentCard
		.btn-toolbar(role='toolbar', aria-label='Toolbar with button groups')
			.btn-group.me-2.mb-1(role='group', aria-label='First group')
				= '\n'
				button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') 1
				= '\n'
				button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') 2
				= '\n'
				button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') 3
				= '\n'
				button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') 4
				= '\n'
			.btn-group.me-2.mb-1(role='group', aria-label='Second group')
				= '\n'
				button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') 5
				= '\n'
				button.btn.btn-dark(type='button') 6
